<L>__{interior jim's classroom day}
<A>__{alone in his room, jim studies the omaha world herald}
<C>__{tracy }
<D>__{he'll probably tell you how committed he was to teaching and democracy and integrity and all. don't be fooled.}
<A>__{after laying the paper down to circle an article, jim leans back in his chair and momentarily loses himself in thought.}
<C>__{jim }
<D>__{it's hard to remember how the whole thing started, the whole election mess. what i do remember is that i loved my job. i was a teacher, an educator, and i couldn't imagine doing anything else.}
<A>__{suddenly a voice }
<C>__{voice }
<D>__{hey, mr. m. mr. m.!}
<A>__{jim glances out the window and sees a kid paul metzler pointing at him. paul walks with a limp. behind him, other students approach the school.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{stop daydreaming! get back to work!}
<A>__{jim enjoys the affectionate joshing and gives the kid a wave. he returns to his newspaper, a contented man.}
<C>__{jim }
<D>__{the students knew it wasn't just a job for me.}
